ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY

Notes: -1 = Screener; 0 = Baseline; 97 = Taper; 98 = Withdrawal; 99 = Interim contact; Otherwise: weeks since baseline

ElementDescription: Study; The code for each individual study
Notes: e.g., the name of the study in multi-grant collections

ElementDescription: ADI: Age at first single words - Interim step to calculate summary scores
Notes: 993 = Had some words, then lost and not yet regained; 994 = Milestone not reached; 996 = N/K, but apparently normal; 997 = N/K, but apparently delayed; 999 = N/K or not asked

ElementDescription: Degree of Control over Compulsive Behavior
Notes: 0 = Complete control; 1 = Much control; 2 = Moderate control; 3 = Little control; 4 = No control
